the wrong I bent, is not the wrong I do, but cannot admit, and as they are my biggest problem, they cannot be those who discuss about me behind the scenes.

As a adult person, as you say we all live a "pre-conceived" fate. Yes, I have the possibility of choice, but I cannot vast money to buy a simple piece of pie, so, I have to submit in order to have something to eat.

I remember another song of Brower (El chaval de los alliados), in there was an episode that reminds many things. What I remember very well is the sour that the politician say while cariciating Brouwer: Assassino del pueblo, lo tenías en la mano, pichanga de mentira, cariñala si puedes.

I want to tell you something else. The Roberto Zanto's song, Lynch, is double-meaning, in Argentina we use the word Lynch in the meaning of abusing. In yesterday discussion it was said almost nothing about that bond; Rozza has his group of supporters and enemies; prior to participating in this affinity group he call Lynch, he abused a little boy without deserve it, and when the little boy took revenge, Rozza decided to kill the"Butcher of Villa Moreno", who is my cousin, Francis Anibal Acuna Pedrozo. Last year a little boy again, called little Francisco, was found dead, finally he was killed by his step father a butcher.
